# Constant Fold Date/Time Functions

## Description

Evaluates deterministic date/time functions at compile time when all
arguments are constants. Functions like EXTRACT, DATE_TRUNC, and
DATE_ADD with literal timestamps and intervals produce known results.

**When to apply**: Deterministic datetime function with constant arguments.
Non-deterministic functions (NOW, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) are excluded.

**Why it works**: DATE_TRUNC('month', TIMESTAMP '2025-03-15') always
returns '2025-03-01'. Computing this once saves per-row work.

## Relational Algebra

```algebra
sigma[EXTRACT(year FROM TIMESTAMP '2025-03-15') = 2025](R)
  -> sigma[2025 = 2025](R)
  -> R  (after boolean folding)
```

## Implementation

```rust
rw!("fold-extract";
    "(extract ?field ?ts)" => { FoldExtract("?field", "?ts") }
    if is_const("?ts")
),
rw!("fold-date-trunc";
    "(date_trunc ?precision ?ts)" => { FoldDateTrunc("?precision", "?ts") }
    if both_const("?precision", "?ts")
),
rw!("fold-date-add";
    "(date_add ?ts ?interval)" => { FoldDateAdd("?ts", "?interval") }
    if both_const("?ts", "?interval")
),
```

## Preconditions

```rust
fn applicable(func_name: &str, args: &[Expr]) -> bool {
    // Must be deterministic (exclude NOW, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, etc.)
    is_deterministic_datetime_fn(func_name)
    && args.iter().all(|a| a.is_literal())
}
```

## Test Cases

```sql
-- Before
SELECT * FROM events
WHERE EXTRACT(year FROM TIMESTAMP '2025-03-15') = 2025;
-- After
SELECT * FROM events WHERE TRUE;
```

```sql
-- Negative: NOW() is non-deterministic
SELECT EXTRACT(year FROM NOW());
-- Cannot fold: NOW() changes per statement
```

